<Layout title="Lesson 7: Robot Subsystems & Technical Pages">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <span class="lesson-badge">Lesson 7</span>
    <h1>Robot Subsystems & Technical Pages</h1>
    <p class="lesson-subtitle">How to document your robot's subsystems and technical components.</p>
    <LessonAudio slug="lesson-6" />
  </div>

  <p>
    This lesson covers how to effectively document your robot's subsystems and technical components.
  </p>

  <h2>What Are Subsystems?</h2>
  <p>
    Subsystems are the individual mechanical, electrical, and software components that make up your robot.
    Each subsystem has a specific purpose and contributes to your robot's overall performance.
  </p>

  <h2>Typical Subsystems</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Drive(train) System</strong>: How your robot moves (wheels, motors, gearing)</li>
    <li><strong>Intake System</strong>: How your robot collects game elements</li>
    <li><strong>Scoring Mechanism</strong>: How your robot scores points</li>
    <li><strong>Hanging/Climbing System</strong>: How your robot hangs or climbs (if applicable)</li>
    <li><strong>Control System</strong>: Sensors and electronics that manage everything</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How to Document Each Subsystem</h2>
  <p>For each subsystem, include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Purpose</strong>: What does this subsystem do?</li>
    <li><strong>Design Evolution</strong>: How did it improve throughout the season?</li>
    <li><strong>Components Used</strong>: Motors, sensors, materials, etc.</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Metrics</strong>: Speed, reliability, efficiency numbers</li>
    <li><strong>Challenges & Solutions</strong>: Problems encountered and how you fixed them</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Allocation Guidelines</h2>
  <p>
    Typically, Robot Subsystems take up <strong>3-5 pages</strong> of your portfolio. Allocate pages based on:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Complexity of each subsystem</li>
    <li>How much the subsystem evolved during the season</li>
    <li>Importance to your team's strategy</li>
    <li>How unique or innovative your solution is</li>
  </ul>

